# UI/UX Rules – Avoid When Building

## 1. No Duplicate Content
- **Avoid** repeating the same section in multiple places (e.g. newsletter signup on both home page and footer).
- **Do** place shared content (newsletter, etc.) in one location—typically the footer for site-wide elements.

## 2. Contrast – Never Dark on Dark
- **Avoid** dark text on dark backgrounds (e.g. `text-white/50`, `text-gray-500` on `#1a1a1a`).
- **Do** use light text (`text-white`, `text-white/90`) on dark backgrounds.
- **Do** use dark text on light backgrounds.
- **Check** footer, hero overlays, and any dark sections for readable text.

## 3. Theme in JSON Only
- **Avoid** hardcoding colors in `globals.css` or inline styles.
- **Do** define all theme values in `config/theme.json`.
- **Do** use `var(--theme-*)` in classNames (e.g. `bg-[var(--theme-footer-bg)]`).
- **Do** use `ThemeStyles` to inject theme from JSON—no theme fallbacks in CSS.

## 4. Text on Image Cards
- **Avoid** light overlays (`bg-black/20`) that make text unreadable on bright images.
- **Do** use a strong bottom gradient: `bg-gradient-to-t from-black/80 via-black/30 to-transparent`.
- **Do** add `drop-shadow-sm` to text overlaying images.
- **Do** use `text-white/90` or `text-white` for secondary text on images.
- **Apply to** category cards, collection cards, hero overlays, and any text-on-image layouts.

## 5. Buttons on Dark Backgrounds
- **Avoid** dark borders on outline buttons over dark backgrounds (e.g. black border on hero).
- **Do** use light borders: `!border-white/70` or `!border-white` for outline buttons on dark sections.
- **Do** use explicit light colors when theme variables might resolve incorrectly.
